<tax:p>Diagnosis.</tax:p>
<tax:p>Male pronotum longer, tegmina almost equal to pronotum, apex truncate (Fig. 20). 10th abdominal tergite with a median notch at middle of hind margin (Fig. 21). Cerci longer, slightly incurved, median portion with one lobe truncated in apex (Fig. 22). Female unknown.</tax:p>
